        (9193, 'Shun Sugata', '1955-02-17', 'Character actor Shun Sugata was born on February 17, 1955 in Yamanashi, Japan as Masamichi Shibuya. Often cast in violent, villainous roles he can be instantly recognized by his deep, gruff voice and imposing stature.  His most notable roles include the intimidating mob enforcer Takayama in Takeshi Miike''s Ichi the Killer  and the corrupt police commissioner in Tokyo Gore Police.

