        (10739, 'Bebe Neuwirth', '1958-12-31', 'From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia.

Beatrice "Bebe" Neuwirth (born December 31, 1958) is an American actress, singer and dancer. She has worked in television and is known for her portrayal of Dr. Lilith Sternin, Dr. Frasier Crane''s wife (later ex-wife), on both the TV sitcom Cheers (in a starring role), and its spin-off Frasier (in a recurring guest role). On stage, she is also known for originating the role of Velma Kelly in the revival of Chicago and for the role of Morticia Addams in The Addams Family musical.', 'Princeton - New Jersey - USA', 1, '/xm58rpMRVDHS0IGttw1pTlqGwkN.jpg'),
        (10742, 'Teri Hatcher', '1964-12-08', 'Teri Lynn Hatcher (born December 8, 1964) is an American actress. She is known for her television roles as Susan Mayer on the ABC comedy-drama series Desperate Housewives, and Lois Lane on the ABC comedy-drama series Lois &amp; Clark: The New Adventures of Superman. In 2005 her Desperate Housewives work won her the Golden Globe Award for Best Actress and the Screen Actor''s Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Female Actress in a Comedy Series.

Description above from the Wikipedia article Teri Hatcher, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.', 'Palo Alto, California, USA', 2, '/xnvUJvf0vjHliYa2PlXyLGaJe9l.jpg'),
        (10743, 'Ricky Jay', '1946-06-26', 'Ricky Jay (born Richard Jay Potash) was an actor, magician, cardsharp, and film consultant. Ricky''s love and deep study of card tricks and deception gained him worldwide fame and respect, and he was often called in to consult for movies and TV shows where deception was a key element of the story. Ricky was an exceptional close-up magician and playing-card handler, but he also acted in movies such as Boogie Nights, Tomorrow Never Dies, and Magnolia, as well as TV shows like the X-Files, HBO''s Deadwood, and David Mamet''s The Unit, always playing intense characters who seemed to know everything but only handed out information in riddles and suggestions.', 'Brooklyn, New York, USA', 1, '/xtJvNUSwIOKZ4Z4SDOYjPhvdtIN.jpg'),
