        (10867, 'Steve Braun', '1976-08-14', 'Steve Braun (born August 14, 1976) is a Canadian television and movie actor from Winnipeg, Manitoba. Braun''s credits include The Immortal, a TV show in which he and co-star Lorenzo Lamas hunted demons; The Trip, a popular independent film about coming of age in the HIV era; and Harold &amp; Kumar Go to White Castle (2004), a major motion picture release in which he plays the lead villain. He also played the role of "Jonsey" in the 2007 thriller movie Wrong Turn 2: Dead End. He also co-starred in the 2005 horror movie "Pterodactyl" as Willis Bradbury.

