        (16427, 'Enrique Castillo', '1949-12-10', 'Castillo was a founding member of The Latino Theater Company. He co-wrote the company’s plays Stone Wedding and August 29. In addition to the plays, he wrote and directed the film The History of The Latino Theater Company, a documentary chronicling the theater company, and co-produced the company’s annual comedy fundraiser Noche de Risa y Susto.  In 1997 Castillo created Four Brown Hats Entertainment (FBHE), a film

