        (18746, 'Stevie Wonder', '1950-05-13', 'Stevland Hardaway Morris (previously Judkins; born May 13, 1950), better known by his stage name Stevie Wonder, is an American singer-songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, record producer and activist. Blind since shortly after birth, Wonder signed with Motown Records'' Tamla label at the age of eleven, and continues to perform and record for Motown to this day.

